Tech question: The laptop I'm borrowing is a Dell Inspiration 2650 and since I'm using it as a regular computer instead of a portable one do you think it's okay to take the battery out? I have noticed the computer gets pretty hot, which I've read is normal for laptops. I have also read the battery can lose life if it's in the heat too long.  My boss, who is letting me borrow the laptop said the battery isn't good anyway, but I don't know how good it is to leave it in if it's going to be plugged in all the time. I've never used a laptop and I'm just wondering about his. And also, is it good to leave the laptop on for hours or should I shut it down after a while. As I said before, I notice it does get hot. It's well ventilated, so that's no issue. I just don't want to ruin anything since it's not my computer.

Have you discovered you had an allergy to something that you didn't know about until that thing cause an allergic reaction?  This is the second time this has happened to me.  The first time was when I took Sulurmeth and found out I'm allergic to sulfur based antibiotics.  
Well, I'm now thinking I might have a latex or adhesive allergy.  I had this boil on the front of my neck and I covered it with this waterproof band aid.  When I took it off this morning, I got this horrible red rash and it started blistering.  I had to go to the gynocologists today anyway, so I thought I'd have him look at it.  He thinks I may have a latex allergy an told me to just monitor the area and put a non latex bandage on it.  I'm not sure he's right, I think I may have an allergy to the adhesive, because I remember when I have had the band aid on my arms it's hard for it to come off.  My skin sticks to tha band aid and it sometimes is hard to come off and sometimes it leaves a red area.  
I'm going to look for an alltergist and see if I can get an appointment to see them.  If not, I will wait until next week when I see the general surgeon to see what he says.  
Right now, it feels like I have a really bad sunburn.  If you have ever had this happen to you, what did you do?

Well, tomorrow is St. Patty's Day.  The day were people get shit faced and listen to great Celtic music.  Yesterday, Buffalo had their annual St. Patty's Day parade on Delaware Ave.  I didn't go, because I went once and there were too many drunken idiots there.  It left a bad taste on my mouth when this woman in a wheelchair was trying to see and a bunch of drunken asswipes wouldn't move.  Sometimes drinking brings the worst out in people.
I'm celebrating St. Pattys Day late, because my Mom's having a corned beef and cabbage dinner next weekend with my aunt, uncle and grandparents.  I'm going to drink Guinness and listen to some great Celtic music.  
I love this time of year, mainly because I can listen to Celtic music. 
If you're going to celebrate tomorrow, don't drink & drive.  :)

I'm so hating how my health has been lately.  I was sick last week.  I was in and out of the ER and I had an allergic reaction to an antibiotic.  I now have UTI and it's causing me havoc.  I hate this and I hate having infections.  I was tested for several things including diabetes.  I'm a candidate for it and I'm going to get help with changing my diet and getting on a better routine.  
I feel fine during the day but at night I am in pain.  I'm going for a GI test next Friday to see how my stomach is holding out.  I totally don't like it.  I'm taking Aleve for the pain, which is tolerable, I guess.  
I just want to go to bed and cry.  :(

My friend, Ghosty has a show on this college station called, WFDU-FM and they are having their pledge drive.  He plays Modern Rock (The Ting Tings, The Killers, Kerli, Goldfrapp) and Classic Alternative (Depeche Mode, Talk Talk, David Bowie, The Damned, Siouxsie and the Banshees).  His show hasn't gotten too many pledges the last weeks and I would love to see people pledge whatever they can afford.  I don't want to see his show go off the air.
To listen to his show, go to http://www.wfdu.fm and if you like his show, call 1-201-692-2012 or you can pledge on the site.  I'd love to see him do well tonight.  So please listen and help out.  I wouldn't do this if I didn't care.  This is the last week to pledge.

Well, since it's fairly quiet here at work due to the weather I thought I'd update my LJ.  I've decided to keep most of it open for now.  I will still have some Friends Only entries, but the majority of things I'll post here are going to be surveys and BlogThings memes.  
I love the winter weather.....NOT.  I got a ride in to work today, which was nice.  Buffalo doesn't close when the weather is bad.  Some places close when there is an inch of snow on the ground.  I know I may bitch and complain sometimes about the weather, but I'd rather take this weather over hurricaines or tornadoes.  
People think Buffalo is the snow capital of the country, but places like Syracuse and Watertown, NY both get more snow than Buffalo does.  It's because Lake Ontario is shallow and it stays warmer than the other lakes.  
I'm glad I live in Buffalo.  :)

1. Pick 15 of your favorite movies.
2. Go to IMDb and find a quote from each movie.
3. Post them here for everyone to guess.
4. Strike it out when someone guesses correctly, and put who guessed it and the movie.
5. NO GOOGLING/using IMDb search or other search functions.

1.  It can't be done. No one's ever taken anyone out of here. Not in the whole history of... the whole history!
2.  Yes. It's in your blood - it's in the blood of ALL Frankensteins. It reaches the soul when words are useless. Your grandfather used to play it to the creature HE vas making.
3.  Sir, you have no call to get snippy with me, I'm just doing my job here.
4.  May I admire you again today? Pretty in Pink
5. Put your flaps down tiger or else you'll take off.
6. Just something I threw together. I call it... Braveheart meets Liberace-Bravache!
7. I really love Rudy. He is totally enamored of me. I mean, I've had other men love me before, but not for six months in a row.  Sixteen Candles
8. What's a little boy like you doing with big boy smut like this?
9. Oh my god, I shot my eye out!  The Christmas Story
10. Sometimes I wish I married a butcher or a plumber.
11. That's a lie! Harry Bailey went to war - he got the Congressional Medal of Honor, he saved the lives of every man on that transport.
12. It happens every time, they all become blueberries.  Willy Wonka and the Chocolate Factory
13. ...'cause you people are BASTARD PEOPLE!
14.  Well you must be very "proud Mary".
15.  No, I tend to just whip it out there. Seems to work best.

I've been going nuts looking for stuff from this band.  They are Lee Harris and Paul Webb from Talk Talk with some help from Beth Gibbons of Portishead and Matt Johnson of The The and other sessions musicians.  
I used to have their CDs, but during some money trouble I traded them in, and I've been looking for their albums: "Herd of Instinct" and "Fields & Waves" ever since.  They have a very techno sound and I loved their music.

It's a week before Christmas and my Mom hasn't decorated yet.  It's not because she doesn't like the holiday, it's because she hasn't had time to do anything.  She has to deal with me, her job and other things.  But this weekend, we will get stuff together and decorate.  
I'm doing better.  I have to do the antibiotics for another three weeks.  It's a bummer, because this means I'll be taking them on Christmas.  Oh well, that's okay.
Christmas this year will be laid back, which I kind of like.  It's just going to be my aunt, uncle, grandparents, my Mom and I.  And I'm really not looking for a lot of presents.  I'm more happy just having my family around than anything.

Yet, tomorrow, I will be joining the masses in shopping.  Why, because I'm insane.  *lol*

From UB Events Calendar. Craig Ferguson Mainstage Theatre Friday, October 5 8:00pm $28, Students $23 Tickets on sale Friday, July 13 at 10AM An Evening of Great Stand-Up Comedy! Craig FergusonCraig Ferguson entered the world of late night comedy following a diverse and eclectic career that encompasses film, television and the stage. Since taking the helm of the Late, Late Show on January 3, 2005, the show has set all-time viewer records. Additionally, Craig recently received his first Emmy nomination for his work on the Late, Late Show. Born in Glasgow, Scotland, Ferguson got his start in the entertainment industry as a drummer for some of the worst punk bands in the U.K., a profession he held for several years. Following his musical stint, he began bartending in a local pub in Glasgow where he was introduced to Michael Boyd, the artistic director of The Tron Theatre in Glasgow, who persuaded Ferguson to give acting a go. After several low paying acting gigs, Ferguson discovered he had a knack for comedy and was soon the star of his own BBC television show, The Ferguson Theory. After several stints on the English comedy circuit, Ferguson brought his act to America in 1995 to star with Betty White and Marie Osmond in the ABC comedy Maybe This Time. After the show ended, ABC decided to add the talented Scotsman to The Drew Carey Show, playing Drew Carey's boss, Nigel Wick, from 1996-2003. SA Logo Ferguson has also starred in, written or directed several feature films. In April 2006, he debuted his first novel entitled Between The Bridge and The River, which became a critically acclaimed bestseller.

Lately, I've been getting several phone calls from this telemarketing agency in Michigan.  I usually screen my calls for telemarketers and I got this # for Phone Bank Systems, the phone # is 517-203-1400 (I normally wouldn't put a phone # here, but I needed to warn you all).  I called the # and left a message for them to stop calling me.  They call at all hours of the day, and they are getting to be too much.  I'm thinking of reporting them to my phone company and the BBB of Michigan (the number is from East Lansing, MI).

The North Tonawanda Police Department has activated the New York State AMBER Alert and is investigating a confirmed child abduction that occurred at 268 Tremont Street, in North Tonawanda at about 8:59 PM on 4/2/2007.

The CHILD, Serenity L. Platts is a White female, approximately 4 years 1 month old with blonde hair and blue eyes. She is approximately 3 feet and weighs about 32 pounds. Serenity was last seen wearing a pink long sleeve sleeper with a Winnie the Pooh emblem and a red fleece.

The SUSPECT, David J. Grover is a White male, approximately 29 years old with brown hair and hazel eyes. He is approximately 5 feet 10 inches tall and weighs about 230 pounds.

The VEHICLE has been identified as a gray 4-door sedan 2003 Acura TL with NY license plate number DLL5964.

Anyone with any information on this abduction is asked to call the North Tonawanda Police Department at (866)NYS-AMBER or dial 911 to provide information on a report or sighting.

This if from my friend Brian (or DJDioFan at Renegade Retro: Allow me to introduce myself to those who may not know me. I am DJ Diofan. I Produce and host Metal Shop on Renegade Retro Which Airs Sundays at 10 PM Eastern. The reason I post this Bulletin is not to promote my show or the station it airs on (Although it couldn't hurt for you to tune in either *Grin* ), No I'm here with an IDEA on how to help save Internet Radio. If you've viewed my profile, or my fellow DJ's Profile, or virtually ANY Internet Radio Station profile on myspace, you know these are perilous times for Internet Radio. As a DJ as well as a Listener of Internet Radio, I came up with a possible Idea for PSA's (For those not fluent in Radio-Speak, PSA means "Public Service Announcement" a form of on-air advertising.) My idea is simply this... DJ's from Affected radio stations (ALL Net Radio in the USA..this is YOU) make a short 1-2 minute PSA about why the CRB Decision should be repealed. Listeners You too can make a PSA...Even if you don't have an MP3 editor..Make a short 1-2 minute voice recording (Preferably Wav or MP3) of what Internet Radio means to you and why you think the CRB ruling should be repealed! (You must give permission in Writing to use your voice for legal reasons.) I think if we all get together on this, We can add another arsenal to the fight against this unfair decision and possibly SAVE Net Radio! You can PM Me on Yahoo Messenger at dj_diofan or visit my profile at RR Metal Shop for more info on contacting me/sending me your PSA. I will see to it that I get the PSA to as many DJ's and Stations as I can!
